DataElement.preferredDefinition: A response to indicate whether a visual imaging examination of the breast density by means of x-rays was performed.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: Visual; relating to or using sight; able to be seen.:Imaging examination of the breast by means of x-rays.

Concepts.definition: Relating to or using sight; able to be seen.

A type of radiography used specifically to examine breast tissue. The procedure utilizes a low-dose of x-rays or radiation to generate an image. A mammography exam or mammogram, is used as a screening tool to detect early breast cancer in women experiencing no symptoms and to detect and diagnose breast disease.
